{
  "text": "Genetic tools have the potential to help solve these problems. Genetic identification of many parasite groups has been possible using the first or second internal transcribed spacers (ITS) of nuclear ribosomal DNA (rDNA; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Genetic tools provide a means by which to identify individual parasites at any stage of the life cycle without morphologic training [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . These tools also provide a means of determining cryptic speciation, generally by analysis of mitochondrial DNA regions (mtDNA; [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] or ITS region sequences .",
  "correct_citation": {
